magpie.attributes.generators

Class LookupTableAttributeGenerator

  • java.lang.Object
    • magpie.attributes.generators.BaseAttributeGenerator
      • magpie.attributes.generators.LookupTableAttributeGenerator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, Options

    public class LookupTableAttributeGenerator
extends BaseAttributeGenerator
    Tool to add precomputed attributes from a lookup table. Use this if you'd like to compute attributes externally and them to a dataset.

    Lookup table should follow the format:

    entry attributeName1 attributeName2 [...] [string describing entry #1] [attribute 1 value] [...]

    When supplied with a dataset, the dataset is first used to parse the strings describing each entry. These are then match to appropriate entries in that dataset. If no matching entry in the lookup table is found for an entry in the dataset, its attributes are set to NaN.

    Usage: <path>
    path: Path to lookup table

    Serialized Form
